    <p>DARYL “ICE­I­CE­ICE” KOH (E-SPORTS)</p>
    <p>The Dota 2 player pock­eted US$313,303 (S$421,164) when his five-mem­ber team, Vici Gam­ing, came in fourth at The In­ter­na­tional 2015.</p>
    <p>NA­TIONAL FOOT­BALL TEAM</p>
    <p>The Li­ons won US$200,000 when they lifted the AFF Suzuki Cup tro­phy in 2012.</p>
    <p>JOEY YEO (BOWL­ING)</p>
    <p>The na­tional kegler was awarded a cheque worth 10 mil­lion yen (S$128,452) when she won the 2015 Bowl­ing World Open in Ja­pan.</p>
    <p>PAUL LIM (DARTS)</p>
    <p>Be­com­ing the first player to hit a per­fect nine-dart fin­ish dur­ing the Embassy World Darts Cham­pi­onship in 1990 earned him £52,000 (S$93,032).</p>
    <p>MARDAN MAMAT (GOLF)</p>
    <p>Win­ning the 2004 In­dian Open saw him walk away with US$50,000.</p>


